"https://res.cloudinary.com/dc5clrqtw/image/upload/v1779680463/lewisrutherfurd_qdqw0r.png"},"residence":{"city":"Hong Kong","country":"Hong Kong SAR"},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"career","header":"Founded Inter-Asia Venture Management, Hong Kong 1972","body":"Lewis Polk Rutherfurd moved to Hong Kong after his 1966 marriage and founded Inter-Asia Venture Management Ltd in 1972 — raising $1 million for his first fund and completing fifteen investments. In 1974 he led the expansion of McDonald's into Hong Kong. He has remained co-founder and Managing Director of the firm for over fifty years, serving also as Vice President of the American Chamber of Commerce in Hong Kong."},{"number":2,"category":"marriage","header":"Married Jackie Kennedy's half-sister Janet Auchincloss","body":"On July 30, 1966 Lewis married Janet Jennings Auchincloss — the half-sister of First Lady Jacqueline Lee Bouvier Kennedy Onassis. They had three children before Janet's death from cancer in 1985 at age forty. The marriage made him brother-in-law to Jackie Kennedy through her mother Janet Lee Auchincloss Bouvier's second marriage to Hugh Auchincloss."},{"number":3,"category":"achievement","header":"Earned Doctor of Business Administration at age 70","body":"In 2015 at age 70, Lewis Polk Rutherfurd completed a Doctor of Business Administration at City University of Hong Kong. His thesis examined pre-deal processes in Asian venture capital funds from 1980 to 2000 — drawing on his own four decades pioneering the field. Inter-Asia Venture Management now oversees five private equity funds focused on China, India, Thailand, Singapore, and Indonesia."}],"slug":"lewis-rutherfurd-1944"}},"burialCemetery":null,"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}